<br>
In my proprosal, I was assuming that geerloks and trophies are additive along with jewelcraft mastery AA and that you could get an effective skill way above 250.  If 252 is truly the maximum, would someone please post a link to a Sony statement to that effect and maybe someone could explain to me why JC Mastery AA has a very measurable effect even if you have 250 skill?  (I'm thinking of the person who posted that they had a 95% success rate with gem studded chains using JCM3.)<br>
<br>
If having 242 skill plus 5% (geerlok or trophy) is truly the maximum, then in my opinion that should be called Grandmaster and I would agree with Merana's statement completely:<br>
<br>
Merana writes, &quot;The point of distinguising grandmaster or not, is so that the customers are ensured that when they are seeking items which require &gt; 250 skill, of which there are numerous in game currently, that they are finding a crafter with the best possible chance for success. Given that, I don't have a problem with someone 242 + 5 mod claiming grandmaster.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=meranaofvazaelle>Merana of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/03 12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How about... &quot;Got trophy?&quot;</span><hr size=1> Numerous discussions on +skill items and their effect on max skill can be found at the message boards on eqtraders.com.  It comes up every few weeks.<br>
<br>
Vaguely from my memory, the reason that they are confident in the answer of 252 max is that it was confirmed as the definitive answer by the tradeskill dev at a recent fan faire.<br>
<br>
Briefly, from the faq:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=42">mboards.eqtraders.com/php...c.php?t=42</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Q: If my skill is 250, would one of these geerlock tools make my skill 262? <br>
A: No, modified skills are capped at 252. In fact, once your skill reaches 240, any skill ups that you get would be meaningless since your skill will be capped at 252. <br>
<br>
<br>
As far as JCM AA goes, it is not like a geerlok/trophy. It does not increase your skill by any percentage.  It reduces your chance of failure on combines by 10, 25 and 50%. Its a subtle but important difference and the skill cap does not apply.  If not for this, then it would be a useless AA for anyone wih 250 skill.  Considering that it costs 18 AA points (3,6,9) to max this, it has to do something other than make you hit the skill cap.  I actually think that this might be broken in the &quot;too good&quot; sort of way, based on what I've seen/heard of results with/without it.<br>
<br>
